        "timestamp": "2018-10-02 10:47:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Jorge\nThis appears to be a timing issue. It works 100% of the time in my local environment but fails intermittently on Jenkins. Adding a 5 second sleep appears to fix the issue.\nCan you add:\nsleep 5\nafter line 29 in plans/policy/apex-pdp/setup.sh\nand also add \"#\" to line24 as this line is intended to be a comment, i.e.\n\n24 #Wait for initialization\n25 for i in {1..10}; do\n26    curl -sS ${APEX_IP}:23324 && break\n27    echo sleep $i\n28    sleep $i\n29 done\n30 sleep 5",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
